fp|t-title|at|Exclusion Beta     (VOID)|fp||at|^^^^|
cp|red|at|^*bOliverC:^*n|cp||at|  Exclusion Beta occurs after a 1@h or 1@s opening and in principle used by 11-13 hcp Responding Hands that have extreme distribution WITH good trump support.

Exclusion Beta shows a VOID in the suit bid, and uses the STRONG Beta Scale, Asking Partner to ignore any controls they might have in the excluded suit.

It's aimed at finding "perfect fit" slams on sub-minimum values where Opener has good controls that aren't wasted in the exclusion suit.

The actual number of hands that will qualify for the use of Exclusion Beta is actually fairly small, because of the way Exclusion Beta actually works.   eg: 

^c 1@s    -   4@d    ^h@2shows  a VOID in @d, excellent trump support, and is Exclusion Beta, asking about the number of Controls Opener has OUTSIDE of @d's.
^b@2|
