cp|red|at|^*bOliverC:^*n|cp||at|  The other use for Exclusion Beta is when Responder has a similar type of hand but with a singleton rather than a void.

Now Responder bids 1NT first and then jump-shifts into their singleton suit over Opener's rebid.

This type of Exclusion Beta tells Opener to counts the Ace of the excluded suit but to ignore the King of that suit.

An example of this kind of hand (after Partner has Opened 1@h might be^^ ^d| 
ih|12  K5432  KQJ32 A2|
lg|c|at|^^
The bidding goes

^c1@h   -   1NT  -   2x   -   3@s    ^k@2the 3@s bid shows the singleton @s, tells Partner to ignore ONLY the @sK   and asks for Controls using the  STRONG  scale.

Again, 5 controls are enough for a small slam and 6 might be enough for a Grand.

^b@2Exclusion Beta ALWAYS agrees Opener's Major, and so (space permitting) Epsilons are permitted over the Beta response.


