fp|t-title|at|After 1NT  and Stayman|fp||at|^^^^|
cp|red|at|^*bOliverC:^*n|cp||at|  There are two Asking Sequence "portals" after Stayman has been used over a 1NT Opening. Ie:
^c@2
1NT  -  2@c  -  2@h  -  3@s  ^j Eta in @h's
1NT  -  2@c  -  2@s  -  3@h  ^j Eta in @s's

^b@2In both of these situations the bid of the OTHER major (other than the one Opener has shown) is ETA in the Major Opener DID bid.

In both cases, Asking Bids are now established and Relay Beta is available over the Eta response, and Epsilons thereafter.
^^^^^^^^|fp|t-title|at|Alpha after 1@d|fp||at|^^^^|
at|Jump-shifts immediately over a 1@d or 1NT Opening by an UNPASSED hand, are Alpha in the suit bid.

These are treated EXACTLY as Alpha over a positive response to 1@c, including the availability of Sigma, its precedence over Relay Beta if/when there is a conflict (eg: over interference).|
