cp|red|at|^*bOliverC:^*n|cp||at|  Last but not least, we come to the Multi-style 2NT Opening.

There are quite a few portals for Asking Bid sequences here: Firstly after 
^c@2
2NT   -   3@c   -   3@d/3@h(Majors)    -     4@c(Gamma in @h)
2NT   -   3@c   -   3@d/3@h(Majors)    -     4@d(Gamma in @s)
^b@2
In each case Asking Bids are now established (so Relay Beta and Epsilons follow).     Similarly, after 
^c@2
2NT   -   3@d(Pref)   -   3@h(Majors) -     4@c(Gamma in @h)      and asking bids are now established
2NT   -   3@d(Pref)   -   3@h(Majors) -     4@d(Gamma in @s)      and asking bids are now established
^b@2
Where Responder bids a Major over 2NT (ie: strongly invitational with that Major and a Minor), there aren't any portals for Asking Bids, because the Major suit bid is itself an Enquiry, asking Opener to clarify their hand-type and range.

Again after the sequence   2NT - 3NT,  the most common continuation is a 4@c bid by Opener, which shows a Major 2-suiter (because with Clubs or the Minors, Opener will usually pass 3NT).        After 

^c2NT  -  3NT  -  4@c  

we rely on a 4@d Enquiry rather than Asking Bids as such, but in all continuations a Beta ask is defined.

Even when Opener DOES continue with both Minors over   2NT - 3NT,   there is always a Beta ask defined, but no other Asking Bids are allowed.|
